NAME
    Tie::Hash::Formatted - A hash containing self-formatting numbers

VERSION
    Version 0.0.1

SYNOPSYS
        use Tie::Hash::Formatted;

        tie my %hash, 'Tie::Hash::Formatted';
        $hash{one} = 1;
        say $hash{one};     # prints "Â£ 1.00"

DEPENDENCIES
    Perl version 5.14.0 or higher

    Tie::Number::Formatted

    Scalar::Util for looks_like_number

SYNTAX
    This ties a hash so that the keys are normal but the values are
    automatically tied to Tie::Number::Formatted if they look like numbers.
    Otherwise they are simply stored as is.

  Tying a hash
        tie my %hash, 'Tie::Hash::Formatted', @options;

  Options
    For all options, see Tie::Number::Formatted. All numbers in the hash
    will be formatted according to these options.

